Definition: an act passed by Congress in 1978 to establish procedures for requesting judicial authorization for foreign intelligence surveillance and to create the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Court
Example: intended to increase United States counterintelligence; separate from ordinary law enforcement surveillance
Synonyms: FISA, legislative_act, an, act, passed, by, Congress, in, to, establish, procedures, for, requesting, judicial, authorization, foreign, intelligence, surveillance, and, create, the, Foreign, Intelligence, Surveillance, Court, intended, increase, United, States, counterintelligence, separate, from, ordinary, law, enforcement
Category: noun.communication
